<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880824-0042 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Ametek Inc. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> AME </CO><IN> BON STK </IN><TEXT>   Ametek Inc., New York, said that Ketema Inc., a new company to be formed from the spinoff of several Ametek businesses, filed a registration statement with the Securities and Exchange Commission covering an offer to stockholders of subordinated debentures.    The debentures will be convertible into Ketema common stock, or Ketema voting preferred stock convertible into common through a rights offering. Ametek didn't specify how much money it expected to raise with the offering.    Under the proposed spinoff, Ametek stockholders will receive one share of Ketema common for every 10 shares of Ametek common that they hold on a record date to be set shortly before the registration statement becomes effective. Ametek stockholders will be entitled to receive one right with each share of Ketema common stock. Other terms of the rights offering, the debentures and the voting preferred stock haven't been fixed, Ametek said.    Ametek, an industrial products maker, currently has about 44 million shares outstanding. </TEXT></DOC>